OpenSolaris/SXCE:

1. install required packages

if you're using OpenSolaris, please make sure you have below
packages installed:

SUNWaconf
SUNWgnu-automake-110
SUNWlibtool
SUNWgmake
SUNWgcc
SUNWgnome-common-devel
SUNWxorg-headers
SUNWusbu

2. setup build enviorment
ln -s /usr/bin/aclocal-1.10 /usr/bin/aclocal
ln -s /usr/bin/automake-1.10 /usr/bin/automake
export PATH=$PATH:/usr/gnu/bin:/usr/sfw/bin

3. run configure scripts
autoreconf

for 64-bit systems, run
./configure --with-linux=yes --enable-xserver64 --libexecdir=/usr/lib/hal

for 32-bit systems, run
./configure --with-linux=yes --libexecdir=/usr/lib/hal

4. build
gmake all

5. install the binaries (as a privileged user)
gmake install

6. restart HAL and Xorg (as a privileged user)
svcadm restart hal
logout the graphical desktop and login again
